🚀 Execution Roadmap
Automated Employee Onboarding & Offboarding System

This roadmap defines how to move from concept → design → build → deploy → scale the system in structured phases.

1. Overview

The execution is divided into 5 phases:

Phase 1 → Planning & Requirements  
Phase 2 → Architecture & Design  
Phase 3 → Core Development  
Phase 4 → Integration & Testing  
Phase 5 → Deployment & Scale

Each phase builds on the previous one.

2. Phase 1: Planning & Requirements
🎯 Objective

Define scope, stakeholders, and system requirements.

Key Activities
Identify stakeholders (HR, IT, Security, Finance)
Define onboarding/offboarding workflows
Document business rules
Define data requirements
Finalize compliance requirements
Deliverables
Requirement Specification Document
Stakeholder Map
Business Rules Document
High-level process flows
3. Phase 2: Architecture & System Design
🎯 Objective

Design system structure and data flow.

Key Activities
Define system architecture (monolith vs microservices)
Design database schema
Define event-driven workflow model
Design IAM integration model
Define API structure
Architecture Components
Workflow Engine
Access Control Service
HR Service
IAM Connector Layer
Audit Logging Service
Deliverables
System Architecture Diagram
Data Architecture Model
API Design Specification
Security Design Document
4. Phase 3: Core Development
🎯 Objective

Build the core system modules.

4.1 Backend Development
Modules:
Employee Service
Workflow Engine
Access Control (RBAC)
Data Integrity Layer
Audit Logging System
Example Development Flow
Employee API → Workflow Trigger → IAM Integration → Audit Log
4.2 Automation Engine
Event dispatcher (NEW_HIRE, EXIT_APPROVED)
Rule engine (business logic enforcement)
Scheduler (time-based automation)
4.3 Data Layer
PostgreSQL (core data)
Object storage (documents)
Event queue (Kafka / RabbitMQ)
Deliverables
Working backend services
Workflow engine
Role-based access system
Database schema implementation
5. Phase 4: Integration & Testing
🎯 Objective

Ensure system works end-to-end.

5.1 Integrations
HR System integration
IAM integration:
Microsoft Entra ID
Okta Identity Platform
Google Workspace
Email/notification systems
Document signing systems
5.2 Testing Types
Unit Testing
Integration Testing
Security Testing
Performance Testing
Workflow End-to-End Testing
5.3 Test Scenarios
Onboarding Flow:
HR → Create Employee → IAM Provision → Role Assignment → Active State

Offboarding Flow:
Exit Approval → Access Revocation → Archival → Audit Log
Deliverables
Fully tested system
Integration validation reports
Security compliance reports
6. Phase 5: Deployment & Scale
🎯 Objective

Deploy system into production and ensure scalability.

6.1 Deployment Strategy
Dev → Staging → Production pipeline
CI/CD automation
Blue-green deployment or rolling updates
6.2 Infrastructure Setup
Cloud platform (AWS / Azure / GCP)
Load balancers
Auto-scaling services
Database replication
6.3 Monitoring & Observability
Logs (audit + system logs)
Metrics dashboards
Alerting system
Error tracking
6.4 Scaling Strategy
Microservices horizontal scaling
Event-driven processing via queues
Read replicas for reporting
Caching layer for performance
7. Timeline Overview
Phase	Duration
Planning	1–2 weeks
Architecture Design	2–3 weeks
Core Development	4–8 weeks
Testing & Integration	2–4 weeks
Deployment & Scaling	1–2 weeks
8. Execution Dependencies
Requirements → Design → Development → Testing → Deployment → Scaling

Each phase must complete before the next begins.

9. Risk Management
Risk	Mitigation
IAM integration failure	Fallback provisioning queue
Workflow breakdown	Retry + rollback mechanism
Data inconsistency	Transactional integrity
Performance bottleneck	Caching + scaling
Security breach	RBAC + audit logs
10. Success Metrics
⏱ Onboarding time reduced by 70%
🔐 Zero unauthorized access events
⚡ 99.9% workflow success rate
📊 Full audit traceability
👥 High user adoption (HR/IT)
